cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the future enhancements of IEEE 802.11be amendment for WiFi 7, which aims to support time-sensitive networking (TSN) capabilities. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the IEEE TSN framework and its components, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use cases presented in the paper, such as industry 4.0 and cloud gaming, could also be relevant to cs.AR (Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
